WEBVTT

00:00.767 --> 00:01.467
<i>michael:
my name is michael westen.</i>

00:02.334 --> 00:03.467
<i>i used to be a spy until...</i>

00:03.534 --> 00:04.901
[ cellphone rings ]

00:04.968 --> 00:07.501
Man: we got a burn notice
on you. you're blacklisted.

00:07.567 --> 00:09.934
<i>when you're burned,
you've got nothing --</i>

00:10.000 --> 00:12.601
<i>no cash, no credit,
no job history.</i>

00:12.667 --> 00:15.200
<i>you're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:15.267 --> 00:16.801
Where am i?
miami.

00:16.868 --> 00:19.701
<i>you do whatever work
comes your way.</i>

00:19.767 --> 00:22.934
<i>you rely on anyone
who's still talking to you.</i>

00:23.000 --> 00:24.300
<i>a trigger-happy
ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.367 --> 00:25.934
Should we shoot them?

00:26.000 --> 00:28.734
<i>...an old friend who used
to inform on you to the fbi...</i>

00:28.801 --> 00:31.133
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.667
<i>...family, too...
hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.734 --> 00:35.834
<i>...if you're desperate.
someone needs your help,
michael.</i>

00:35.901 --> 00:38.334
<i>bottom line --
as long as you're burned,</i>

00:38.400 --> 00:40.033
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:49.868 --> 00:51.634
<i>whether you're
hunting down extremists</i>

00:51.701 --> 00:53.300
<i>in the mountains of kashmir</i>

00:53.367 --> 00:56.067
<i>or tracking arms dealers
through the streets of moscow,</i>

00:56.133 --> 00:59.200
<i>the life of a spy takes a toll.</i>

01:05.901 --> 01:08.200
<i>so during downtimes,
you work out, eat right,</i>

01:08.267 --> 01:09.667
<i>and try to recharge
your batteries,</i>

01:09.734 --> 01:11.434
<i>because you never know
what's waiting for you</i>

01:11.501 --> 01:12.734
<i>around the next corner.</i>

01:14.234 --> 01:15.667
Fiona:
hello, michael.

01:15.734 --> 01:17.801
This is bud --
bail jumper.

01:17.868 --> 01:20.200
We just got back from a lovely
time in the everglades.

01:20.267 --> 01:22.033
You have a real chair
in this dump?

01:22.100 --> 01:24.734
Poor bud's in a bad
mood. he didn't like
the music in my trunk.

01:24.801 --> 01:25.767
Why is he here?

01:27.133 --> 01:29.334
Oh, we're killing time,

01:29.400 --> 01:32.434
Waiting for the bail bondsman
to open his office.

01:32.501 --> 01:34.701
You know, he's been
throwing me more jobs

01:34.767 --> 01:36.200
Than i can manage lately,

01:36.267 --> 01:39.133
And i was thinking, as long
as you're still burned...

01:39.200 --> 01:41.234
Trudging through swamps,
looking for guys like bud?

01:41.300 --> 01:42.801
<i>i'm not hurting for money
that bad, fi.</i>

01:42.868 --> 01:44.901
[ scoffs ]
could have fooled me.

01:44.968 --> 01:47.234
Think about it, michael.

01:47.300 --> 01:49.767
Your strategic know-how...

01:49.834 --> 01:52.133
My expertise in the field.

01:52.200 --> 01:53.834
My brains, your brawn.

01:53.901 --> 01:55.434
[ scoffs ]
[ whoosh ]

01:55.501 --> 01:57.634
Time for you to go, bud.

02:02.901 --> 02:05.467
Mr. westen,
detective paxson, miami p.d.

02:05.534 --> 02:06.901
This is detective lopez.

02:06.968 --> 02:08.934
You mind if we ask you
a couple questions?

02:09.000 --> 02:10.633
I'm in the middle
of something, actually.

02:10.701 --> 02:11.934
Hmm.

02:12.000 --> 02:14.033
I understand you're a bounty
hunter, miss glenanne.

02:14.100 --> 02:16.033
Do you have
a bail-enforcer's license?

02:16.100 --> 02:17.501
Uh, actually,
i'm freelancing.

02:19.968 --> 02:21.567
Actually, you're
harboring a fugitive.

02:21.634 --> 02:23.133
Consider this a warning.

02:23.200 --> 02:24.767
Michael: uh, detective,

02:24.834 --> 02:27.534
I spoke with some officers
at the station recently,

02:27.601 --> 02:30.334
And i think we cleared up
all the questions they had.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.000
Well, i have
different questions.

02:32.067 --> 02:33.734
They're about
a traffic incident --

02:33.801 --> 02:36.501
Three cars blown up,
three more totaled.

02:36.567 --> 02:39.901
Apparently, we have a one-man
wrecking crew on our hands.

02:39.968 --> 02:41.801
Well, how can you be
so sure it's a man?

02:41.868 --> 02:44.434
I'm as progressive as
the next gal, miss glenanne,

02:44.501 --> 02:46.901
But someone matching
mr. westen's description

02:46.968 --> 02:49.133
Was spotted driving away
from the scene.

02:49.200 --> 02:50.400
White male, dark hair...

02:50.467 --> 02:52.267
[ clears throat ]
...athletically built?

02:52.334 --> 02:53.901
I hope your department
pays overtime,

02:53.968 --> 02:55.667
Because you're
gonna be searching

02:55.734 --> 02:57.467
For a few hundred thousand
suspects.

02:57.534 --> 02:59.000
I've got just one.

02:59.067 --> 03:00.868
Stuff's been blowing up
pretty steadily

03:00.934 --> 03:02.434
Since you arrived in miami.

03:02.501 --> 03:05.067
So, are you gonna
answer my questions,

03:05.133 --> 03:07.567
Or am i gonna pick my way
through everything you own?

03:07.634 --> 03:10.534
That would be a workbench,
six power tools,

03:10.601 --> 03:12.033
Four yogurts --
three yogurts.

03:12.100 --> 03:14.334
I actually had one.
blueberry.

03:14.400 --> 03:18.133
Well, you can tell me
all about it at the
station, mr. westen.

03:18.200 --> 03:19.667
Get in the car.

03:19.734 --> 03:22.234
I'm gonna enjoy this.

03:30.400 --> 03:33.067
Welcome to your worst
nightmare, mr. westen.

03:55.200 --> 03:56.934
You look wretched, michael.

03:57.000 --> 03:59.601
Well, it's not a day spa
in there, fi.

03:59.667 --> 04:02.434
Spent the last 24 hours
in the drunk tank.

04:02.501 --> 04:05.801
So, detective paxson wasn't
questioning you the whole time?

04:05.868 --> 04:08.133
Oh, no, there was
plenty of that, too.

04:08.200 --> 04:12.033
[ sighs ] she's gonna be
some real trouble.

04:12.100 --> 04:14.000
She already is.
she cost me my bounty.

04:14.067 --> 04:15.701
I'll make it up
to you sometime.

04:15.767 --> 04:17.601
Well, how does now sound?
i lined up a new gig.

04:17.666 --> 04:19.466
I'll fill you in on all
the details over lunch.

04:19.534 --> 04:21.334
Come on, fi.
not another bail jumper.

04:21.399 --> 04:24.734
No, but one of my old
bail jumpers got me the job.

04:24.801 --> 04:26.334
It's a referral.

04:35.100 --> 04:36.934
So, how's stevie?

04:37.000 --> 04:38.601
Doing time up at raiford
medium-security.

04:38.667 --> 04:40.300
Says "hi," by the way.

04:40.367 --> 04:42.934
Her brother jumped bail
on forgery charges.

04:43.000 --> 04:44.467
I chased him to boca.

04:44.534 --> 04:46.367
Had to hit him with a brick
to get him in the car.

04:46.434 --> 04:47.501
Sweet guy.

04:47.567 --> 04:48.634
He your partner?

04:48.701 --> 04:50.501
Well, you'd have to
ask him that.

04:50.567 --> 04:51.968
What can we
help you with?

04:52.033 --> 04:54.467
[ sighs ]
this is my son, brandon.

04:54.534 --> 04:56.567
He's been staying
with his dad, howard.

04:56.634 --> 04:58.100
We're separated.

04:58.167 --> 05:01.367
Howard hasn't let me see or talk
to brandon for three days.

05:01.434 --> 05:03.934
Well, it sounds like
you should be talking
to a lawyer about this.

05:04.000 --> 05:05.601
I have -- three of them.

05:05.667 --> 05:08.434
They all say it'll take months
to get him into court.

05:08.501 --> 05:11.100
Howard just needs someone
to knock some sense into him.

05:11.167 --> 05:12.767
--
it's not a problem.

05:12.834 --> 05:15.133
Anything else you need?

05:15.200 --> 05:17.300
I just want to see my son.

05:17.367 --> 05:18.801
Everything will be fine.

05:18.868 --> 05:20.067
Right, michael?

05:21.601 --> 05:24.400
[ horn honking ]

05:24.467 --> 05:25.300
Excuse me.

05:28.033 --> 05:30.367
Do you know my new girl?

05:30.434 --> 05:32.534
She rebuilt this
engine by herself.

05:32.601 --> 05:33.868
I'm telling you,

05:33.934 --> 05:36.200
Just put a nice, sturdy tool
in that woman's hand --

05:36.267 --> 05:38.767
I got it, sam.
find out anything?

05:38.834 --> 05:41.901
Yeah, i asked around
about your lady detective.

05:41.968 --> 05:44.501
Turns out you got
a stalker with a badge.

05:44.567 --> 05:47.267
I mean, she checked
every self-storage place

05:47.334 --> 05:48.934
From here up to
fort lauderdale.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.634
She found some
surveillance video

05:50.701 --> 05:52.901
Of you ducking into
a place down by homestead.

05:52.968 --> 05:54.601
Not good.
what you got there?

05:54.667 --> 05:56.334
Some c-4 and detonators.

05:56.400 --> 05:59.033
Well, she's gonna own
them soon, 'cause she's
working on a warrant.

05:59.100 --> 06:00.634
There's a hearing
in a couple of days,

06:00.701 --> 06:02.868
But you got to get your stash
out of there before then.

06:02.934 --> 06:04.234
Fiona:
are you coming, michael?

06:04.300 --> 06:05.868
Oh, mike,
uh, you know,

06:05.934 --> 06:07.767
Since i'm helping you
avoid felony charges,

06:07.834 --> 06:10.167
I thought maybe there'd
be a lunch in it for me.

06:10.234 --> 06:12.033
Michael?

06:12.100 --> 06:13.467
Next time.

06:15.634 --> 06:17.634
Geez.

06:17.701 --> 06:18.934
<i>i got you, baby.</i>

06:23.734 --> 06:25.100
Patricia: typical.

06:25.167 --> 06:27.267
Howard spends 80 hours
a week at the office,

06:27.334 --> 06:29.501
And he can't find an hour
to take care of his yard.

06:29.567 --> 06:31.868
[ cellphone ringing ]

06:31.934 --> 06:34.267
Fiona:
go ahead and take it.

06:34.334 --> 06:35.734
Just keep your eyes
on the street.

06:35.801 --> 06:39.868
This should be pretty
straightforward.

06:39.934 --> 06:41.434
Yeah, ma?

06:41.501 --> 06:44.601
It's somebody's
birthday today.

06:44.667 --> 06:46.267
I thought you could come over
for a nice dinner

06:46.334 --> 06:47.868
With sam and fiona.

06:47.934 --> 06:50.100
We're celebrating
birthdays now?

06:50.167 --> 06:52.634
We always did.
don't you remember sixth grade?

06:52.701 --> 06:54.567
Your friend billy kane
was there.

06:54.634 --> 06:56.067
<i>it was his party, mom.</i>

06:56.133 --> 06:58.100
Well, it's never too late.

06:58.167 --> 07:01.067
All right, where are we
getting takeout from?

07:01.133 --> 07:03.200
Who said anything
about takeout?

07:03.267 --> 07:04.467
[ paper hits floor ]

07:04.534 --> 07:05.968
Howard!

07:06.033 --> 07:08.167
So, you coming or not?
i'll try.

07:08.234 --> 07:11.400
Michael, i don't want
to hear how you'll try.
i want you to promise.

07:11.467 --> 07:13.801
<i>fine.
i promise i'll try.</i>

07:13.868 --> 07:15.400
Howard!

07:21.634 --> 07:22.834
[ engine turns over ]

07:22.901 --> 07:24.534
[ tires squeal ]

07:36.601 --> 07:37.567
You can stop now.

07:39.767 --> 07:41.200
You can stop now!

07:48.367 --> 07:51.200
Ugh! oh!

07:51.267 --> 07:54.400
Howard...

07:54.467 --> 07:55.834
We just want
to see your son.

07:55.901 --> 07:57.734
Oh, you don't understand.

07:57.801 --> 08:00.067
I'm sure whatever the
issue is, you can work
it out with your ex.

08:00.133 --> 08:03.501
No! that's not
what i mean.

08:03.567 --> 08:04.868
He was kidnapped.

08:04.934 --> 08:08.133
Of course he was.

08:08.200 --> 08:11.434
Brandon didn't come home
from school on thursday.

08:11.501 --> 08:14.100
I got a call. uh, i don't
know the guy's name.

08:14.167 --> 08:15.334
Is he asking for money?

08:15.400 --> 08:18.067
No, i-i-i work
at a diamond wholesaler.

08:18.133 --> 08:22.234
He wanted information
about an upcoming shipment.

08:22.300 --> 08:23.934
Said not to contact
the police,

08:24.000 --> 08:25.701
Or i'd never...

08:25.767 --> 08:27.834
See brandon again.

08:29.734 --> 08:31.267
He's calling today
with instructions.

08:31.334 --> 08:32.634
How could you
not tell me?

08:32.701 --> 08:35.167
I didn't want you calling
the police, patricia.

08:35.234 --> 08:36.634
I was trying
to protect brandon.

08:36.701 --> 08:38.501
That was not your decision
to make! he's my son, too!

08:38.567 --> 08:42.567
Look, he just wants diamonds.
i'm going to give them to him.

08:42.634 --> 08:44.434
Howard,
it's not that simple.

08:44.501 --> 08:46.334
If this guy really
wants to disappear,

08:46.400 --> 08:48.267
He has no incentive
to return your son.

08:48.334 --> 08:51.434
Brandon's old enough
to identify him.

08:51.501 --> 08:53.367
Whoa, whoa, w-what --
what are you saying?

08:53.434 --> 08:55.334
You know what
he's saying, howard.

08:55.400 --> 08:57.234
They're not gonna bring us
brandon back alive!

08:57.300 --> 08:58.467
We should call the police.
no!

08:58.534 --> 09:00.501
No cops!
he said he would kill him.

09:00.567 --> 09:01.868
Enough.

09:01.934 --> 09:03.667
Michael and i will
take care of him...

09:07.267 --> 09:09.534
...without involving
the cops.

09:09.601 --> 09:11.501
But you can't be at
each other's throats, okay?

09:11.567 --> 09:13.200
When the kidnapper
calls again,

09:13.267 --> 09:15.434
You're going to say
you're not doing anything

09:15.501 --> 09:18.000
Until you get proof that
your son is alive and unhurt,

09:18.067 --> 09:20.434
And then you're gonna ask
for a face-to-face meeting.

09:20.501 --> 09:21.834
You think he'll come?

09:21.901 --> 09:23.667
If he wants his diamonds,
he will.

09:23.734 --> 09:25.734
And if we're lucky,
we'll follow him back
to where brandon is.

09:25.801 --> 09:27.601
Well, won't that
be dangerous?

09:27.667 --> 09:29.734
It doesn't matter.
i'll do it.

09:29.801 --> 09:31.934
Whatever it takes
to get brandon back.

09:40.400 --> 09:43.534
I told howard not to take
that stupid job.

09:43.601 --> 09:45.200
Sales manager.

09:45.267 --> 09:46.968
We were doing
just fine as reps.

09:47.033 --> 09:48.934
You work together?
we did.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.400
It was great till
he took that promotion.

09:51.467 --> 09:55.033
Long hours, travel,
and now this.

09:55.100 --> 09:56.868
<i>well, i'm sure this
was not part of the plan</i>

09:56.934 --> 09:58.133
When he took the job.

09:58.200 --> 09:59.534
Well, he should have
known the risk.

10:02.901 --> 10:04.501
Patricia, i want you
to try something.

10:04.567 --> 10:09.234
It's a relaxation exercise
i do in situations like this.

10:09.300 --> 10:11.834
I want you
to close your eyes...

10:11.901 --> 10:14.367
And breathe deep.

10:14.434 --> 10:15.968
Picture a peaceful
mountain stream.

10:16.033 --> 10:17.000
Can you do that?

10:18.901 --> 10:20.934
Now picture yourself...

10:21.000 --> 10:23.033
Drowning the kidnapper
in the stream.

10:23.100 --> 10:25.501
You're taking a rock
from the stream

10:25.567 --> 10:27.167
And raising it
above your head...
michael: fi.

10:27.234 --> 10:29.033
...and with tremendous force,
you're bringing --

10:29.100 --> 10:30.601
Fi!

10:30.667 --> 10:33.467
We got something.
he's passed by twice.

10:33.534 --> 10:35.367
<i>smart criminals
have a variety of ways</i>

10:35.434 --> 10:38.934
<i>to find out if a meeting
is under police surveillance.</i>

10:39.000 --> 10:40.400
<i>some are more subtle
than others.</i>

10:40.467 --> 10:42.801
Howard, right?
yeah.

10:42.868 --> 10:44.334
I'm santora.

10:44.400 --> 10:46.400
Nice to meet you.

10:46.467 --> 10:48.434
Ugh! oh! oh!

10:48.501 --> 10:50.567
<i>throw a few punches...</i>

10:50.634 --> 10:53.801
<i>and any cops in the area
have to come running.</i>

10:53.868 --> 10:55.334
God! do something!

10:55.400 --> 10:57.000
We can't.
he's testing us.

10:57.067 --> 10:59.033
But he's gonna kill him!
he's --

10:59.100 --> 11:01.534
Whoa.
patricia. patricia!

11:01.601 --> 11:03.934
If you want your son back,
you'll stay in the car.

11:07.534 --> 11:10.067
You got any friends around here
i should know about?

11:10.834 --> 11:12.300
Ugh!

11:12.367 --> 11:14.667
You tell anyone about
our little arrangement?

11:14.734 --> 11:17.367
[ groans ]
look at me, howard.

11:17.434 --> 11:21.033
<i>behavior in a combat situation
is unpredictable.</i>

11:21.100 --> 11:24.133
<i>sometimes trained soldiers
go screaming for the hills.</i>

11:24.200 --> 11:26.400
<i>sometimes guys
who have never fired</i>

11:26.467 --> 11:28.367
<i>anything bigger than a cap gun</i>

11:28.434 --> 11:31.801
<i>turn out to have
ice in their veins.</i>

11:31.868 --> 11:33.467
[ breathing heavily ]

11:33.534 --> 11:35.767
Nobody knows.

11:35.834 --> 11:38.300
Let me see my son.

11:45.067 --> 11:48.234
Today's headline.
the kid's fine.

11:48.300 --> 11:50.000
Now, let's be clear.

11:50.067 --> 11:51.467
You're not calling
the shots here.

11:51.534 --> 11:53.968
You're not gonna make
any more demands,

11:54.033 --> 11:55.901
And you're not gonna
try anything cute.

11:55.968 --> 11:57.601
If anyone touches me,

11:57.667 --> 12:00.701
If i'm a minute late
checking in with my guys,

12:00.767 --> 12:02.000
You never see
the kid again.

12:02.067 --> 12:03.501
Got it?

12:03.567 --> 12:05.334
Yeah.

12:05.400 --> 12:06.767
Good.

12:06.834 --> 12:08.734
Ugh!

12:08.801 --> 12:10.434
That's just
so you don't forget.

12:10.501 --> 12:13.334
Now...

12:13.400 --> 12:15.234
Let's talk
about my diamonds.

12:15.300 --> 12:17.734
<i>in the field, it's often
your human instincts</i>

12:17.801 --> 12:19.400
<i>that jeopardize an operation.</i>

12:19.467 --> 12:21.000
<i>helping people is great,</i>

12:21.067 --> 12:23.834
<i>but there are times that
impulse can get people killed.</i>

12:23.901 --> 12:27.934
<i>sometimes the right thing to do
is let a guy bleed for a while.</i>

12:30.367 --> 12:31.834
Stay here.

12:42.067 --> 12:43.534
[ moans ]

12:43.601 --> 12:45.567
He kept hitting me.
i didn't know what to do.

12:45.634 --> 12:47.200
You did everything right,
howard.

12:47.267 --> 12:49.033
He said he wants the stones
in 24 hours...

12:49.100 --> 12:51.000
Or brandon dies.

12:51.067 --> 12:52.834
That's not gonna happen.

13:02.300 --> 13:04.400
How'd we do?

13:04.467 --> 13:07.000
Uh, not so great.

13:07.067 --> 13:09.133
Santora didn't
go near the kid.

13:09.200 --> 13:11.701
He's hanging out at a bar,
sipping mojitos.

13:11.767 --> 13:14.300
Mike, this guy's
not afraid to be seen.

13:14.367 --> 13:16.701
But i thought you could follow
him to where brandon is.

13:16.767 --> 13:17.934
I thought --
he's smart.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.334
He's keeping the job
compartmentalized.

13:20.400 --> 13:22.701
Howard's at the hospital
getting stitches.

13:22.767 --> 13:24.033
That was all for nothing?!

13:24.100 --> 13:25.467
Not nothing.
we'll know when he moves.

13:25.534 --> 13:26.934
I got a buddy
keeping an eye on him.

13:27.000 --> 13:29.901
Why can't you just grab him and
waterboard him or something,

13:29.968 --> 13:31.701
Make him tell us
where brandon is?

13:31.767 --> 13:32.868
You torture somebody,

13:32.934 --> 13:34.968
They'll tell you anything
to make it stop.

13:35.033 --> 13:37.501
No, there are better ways
to get reliable information.

13:37.567 --> 13:39.434
Sam, how do you feel
about a little...

13:39.501 --> 13:40.734
Reverse interrogation?

13:40.801 --> 13:42.300
Never been a big fan, mike.

13:42.367 --> 13:43.767
What's reverse
interrogation?

13:43.834 --> 13:45.434
We used to do it
during the cold war.

13:45.501 --> 13:47.634
You send one of your guys
in there to be interrogated

13:47.701 --> 13:49.534
To learn what the bad guys
are worried about.

13:49.601 --> 13:50.934
You play your cards right,

13:51.000 --> 13:52.501
Their questions will tell you
all about them.

13:52.567 --> 13:53.934
You play
your cards wrong --

13:54.000 --> 13:55.367
Have a little faith, sam.

13:55.434 --> 13:57.667
How long do you think
it'll take to set up?

13:57.734 --> 13:59.934
Car, building...

14:00.000 --> 14:01.934
Some cop lights --
a couple hours.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.534
All right, call me
when it's done.

14:04.601 --> 14:08.367
We're gonna find your son.

14:18.834 --> 14:21.334
This is a valuable
lesson for you.

14:21.400 --> 14:23.367
C-4 is meant to be used,
not stored.

14:23.434 --> 14:24.767
I'll keep that in mind.

14:24.834 --> 14:26.334
I'm serious.

14:26.400 --> 14:28.167
All those times you told me
to make the explosions smaller,

14:28.234 --> 14:29.634
I shouldn't have
listened to you,

14:29.701 --> 14:31.634
Then paxson wouldn't have
anything to hang you with.

14:31.701 --> 14:33.033
<i>when you're concerned</i>

14:33.100 --> 14:35.534
<i>you might be walking
into a police stakeout,</i>

14:35.601 --> 14:38.000
<i>there are a number of things
to look out for --</i>

14:38.067 --> 14:39.801
<i>parked cars or vans...</i>

14:39.868 --> 14:42.200
Hold on, fi.

14:42.267 --> 14:44.667
<i>...workers that seem
unusually preoccupied...</i>

14:44.734 --> 14:47.434
<i>and curious kids.</i>

14:47.501 --> 14:49.033
<i>no matter where you go
in the world,</i>

14:49.100 --> 14:52.701
<i>little boys
like candy, puppies, and cops.</i>

14:52.767 --> 14:56.968
I think our detective friend
had a surprise planned.

15:00.934 --> 15:02.267
Mr. westen.

15:02.334 --> 15:04.868
Detective paxson and
detective forget-your-name.

15:04.934 --> 15:07.200
You know, i was thinking
about renting one of
these storage units.

15:07.267 --> 15:08.701
You mind if i look at yours?

15:08.767 --> 15:09.901
Storage unit?

15:09.968 --> 15:11.200
Yes, or you could give us

15:11.267 --> 15:13.234
The fake name you used
when you rented it.

15:13.300 --> 15:17.434
Or go ahead and clear it out.
don't let us stop you.

15:17.501 --> 15:20.334
I think there's been
a big misunderstanding.

15:20.400 --> 15:22.400
I actually heard
you were in the neighborhood,

15:22.467 --> 15:23.834
And i came by to see you.

15:23.901 --> 15:25.467
Yeah, i wanted to give you
some receipts --

15:25.534 --> 15:26.767
You know,
give you a better idea

15:26.834 --> 15:28.501
Of what i've been doing,
where i've been going.

15:28.567 --> 15:31.000
That one's for breakfast.
fi had a spanish omelet.

15:31.067 --> 15:33.300
Egg whites only.
thank you.

15:33.367 --> 15:36.634
Well, if you get the urge
to destroy any evidence,

15:36.701 --> 15:38.267
Stop by.

15:38.334 --> 15:40.300
We'll be waiting for you.

15:43.701 --> 15:45.934
Was that flirting,
or does she hate you?

15:46.000 --> 15:47.367
I am not her type.

15:47.434 --> 15:50.200
[ cellphone ringing ]

15:50.267 --> 15:51.400
Yeah, sam?

15:51.467 --> 15:54.067
Hey, mike, you ready
to do this? i'm all set.

15:54.133 --> 15:56.767
Seriously, though, i think
this is a little risky.

15:56.834 --> 15:59.133
I'm on my way.

16:00.534 --> 16:03.067
[ siren wailing ]

16:04.934 --> 16:08.267
<i>when it comes to cover i.d.s,
impersonating a bad cop</i>

16:08.334 --> 16:10.300
<i>is much better than
impersonating a good one.</i>

16:10.367 --> 16:13.234
<i>an honest cop follows
policies and procedures,</i>

16:13.300 --> 16:15.801
<i>from the way he cuts his hair
to the approach he takes</i>

16:15.868 --> 16:17.334
<i>when carrying out
a traffic stop.</i>

16:17.400 --> 16:19.801
<i>pose as a good cop,
and you have to go by the book.</i>

16:19.868 --> 16:21.734
<i>pose as a bad cop,</i>

16:21.801 --> 16:23.434
<i>and you can throw out that book
and write your own.</i>

16:23.501 --> 16:27.200
Hi, there.
detective finley.

16:27.267 --> 16:29.601
Wow, nice seats.

16:29.667 --> 16:31.267
What is that,
pearl leather?

16:31.334 --> 16:34.200
Let me call my lawyer.
he can tell you all about them.

16:34.267 --> 16:36.234
[ chuckling ]
all right, just relax.

16:36.300 --> 16:38.634
I'm here unofficially.

16:38.701 --> 16:41.968
Just think of this as...
a business meeting.

16:42.033 --> 16:43.634
You want to do
a business meeting?

16:43.701 --> 16:45.234
How about you make
an appointment?

16:45.300 --> 16:46.634
[ chuckling ] okay.

16:46.701 --> 16:48.200
When's a good time
to talk about someone

16:48.267 --> 16:49.934
Who's trying to move in
on one of your scores?

16:50.000 --> 16:51.834
Just worked a drug bust.

16:51.901 --> 16:53.901
Heard something that
might interest you.

16:55.400 --> 16:58.701
<i>in the criminal world,
selling yourself as a colleague</i>

16:58.767 --> 17:01.300
<i>often means
doing something illegal.</i>

17:01.367 --> 17:05.032
<i>so while snorting lactose
isn't pleasant...</i>

17:05.099 --> 17:08.067
[ snorts ]

17:08.133 --> 17:10.467
<i>...it may put
people's minds at ease.</i>

17:10.534 --> 17:12.567
Oh ho! got this
on the bust, too.

17:12.634 --> 17:15.067
[ sniffles ]
90% pure. mmm!

17:15.133 --> 17:17.300
Puts hair on your chest,
i'll tell you that.

17:17.367 --> 17:20.267
What's this you heard
about a score?

17:20.334 --> 17:22.334
Yeah, it was a coke buy
down in overtown.

17:22.400 --> 17:24.300
Busted a guy i know,
a junkie named shep.

17:24.367 --> 17:26.233
So, he's trying
to get me to lay off him

17:26.300 --> 17:28.300
'cause he says he knows
something about a plan

17:28.367 --> 17:30.567
To, uh, rip you off.

17:30.634 --> 17:32.868
Some junkie told you this?

17:32.934 --> 17:34.234
Yeah, he's a snitch.

17:34.300 --> 17:36.434
Hey, the guy's a mess,
but his intel's usually good.

17:36.501 --> 17:37.901
So, why'd you bust him?

17:37.968 --> 17:40.133
Well, i take him in every so
often just to keep him in line.

17:40.200 --> 17:44.467
So, listen, i'm taking
him to the station.

17:44.534 --> 17:46.501
For a couple of grand...

17:46.567 --> 17:49.167
You can question him first.

17:49.234 --> 17:50.334
Interested?

17:53.934 --> 17:57.167
He said something about a kid,
if that means anything.

17:57.234 --> 17:59.367
A kid?

17:59.434 --> 18:01.701
Yeah, he didn't say
much more than that.

18:01.767 --> 18:03.767
Man, i cannot
get over this leather.

18:03.834 --> 18:05.501
It's hand-tooled, right?

18:05.567 --> 18:07.000
Where is this guy?

18:07.067 --> 18:09.467
Madeline:
so, what you're saying is,

18:09.534 --> 18:12.834
Michael's missing
his own birthday party?!

18:12.901 --> 18:14.501
H-he's busy.

18:14.567 --> 18:15.734
Busy?

18:15.801 --> 18:18.601
Busy being shot at
or busy get blown up?

18:18.667 --> 18:20.734
Does he ever
take a day off?

18:20.801 --> 18:24.734
Ow! damn it!

18:24.801 --> 18:26.300
I mean, you know...

18:26.367 --> 18:28.167
A little consideration
is all i'm asking.

18:28.234 --> 18:31.400
I'm making an effort.
so should he.

18:31.467 --> 18:34.534
Well, he seems to be
making progress.

18:34.601 --> 18:36.667
Don't fool yourself, honey.

18:36.734 --> 18:41.200
Loving michael
is always trench warfare.

18:41.267 --> 18:45.467
Hmm.

18:45.534 --> 18:49.067
You tell him
to come to the party.

19:01.000 --> 19:04.100
Sam:
busted a few raves here.

19:04.167 --> 19:06.133
Don't worry.
no one comes around now.

19:06.200 --> 19:07.667
Place is condemned.

19:07.734 --> 19:10.334
It's where i do
my, uh, freelance work.

19:10.400 --> 19:13.234
So, the snitch is in there.
you got my money?

19:14.667 --> 19:16.567
Here you go.
i'll take it from here.

19:16.634 --> 19:18.000
Oh, oh, no, my friend.

19:18.067 --> 19:19.901
That's not how it works.

19:19.968 --> 19:21.334
We question
this guy together.

19:21.400 --> 19:24.934
No offense, but i don't like
people knowing my business.

19:25.000 --> 19:26.534
Yeah, no offense,
but i don't care.

19:26.601 --> 19:28.133
Your business doesn't
concern me.

19:28.200 --> 19:30.601
What concerns me is nobody
touches my prisoner but me.

19:30.667 --> 19:32.033
I got my own way
of asking questions.

19:32.100 --> 19:34.000
Yeah, and i got to explain
every scratch on the guy

19:34.067 --> 19:35.634
When i take him
down to the station.

19:35.701 --> 19:38.033
So if you want to come down
there with me, that's fine.

19:38.100 --> 19:39.334
Otherwise,
we do this my way.

19:39.400 --> 19:42.033
And what about later?

19:42.100 --> 19:43.734
This guy shep
gets to mouth off?

19:43.801 --> 19:45.634
[ laughs ]
don't worry about that.

19:45.701 --> 19:48.200
I got enough on this guy to send
him to prison on the moon.

19:48.267 --> 19:51.701
He'll keep his mouth shut.

19:51.767 --> 19:54.100
Santora: so, nobody knows you
got this guy here, huh?

19:54.167 --> 19:56.100
Sam: [ chuckles ]
don't get any ideas.

19:56.167 --> 19:58.200
As far as my
supervisor's concerned,

19:58.267 --> 20:00.033
I'm working on a case.

20:00.100 --> 20:02.367
Officially, i'm in the middle
of interviewing you,

20:02.434 --> 20:04.000
So if anything
happens to me,

20:04.067 --> 20:05.734
He knows who to
come looking for.

20:05.801 --> 20:07.968
Let's do this.

20:08.033 --> 20:10.467
So, i don't know you...

20:10.534 --> 20:12.567
But i hear you know me...

20:12.634 --> 20:14.834
And my business.

20:14.901 --> 20:17.400
<i>interrogation professionals
don't ask questions directly.</i>

20:17.467 --> 20:20.234
<i>they hide what they know
and don't know.</i>

20:20.300 --> 20:22.601
Aw, you're a real prince,
finley,

20:22.667 --> 20:25.033
A real stand-up guy.

20:25.100 --> 20:26.868
After all i've done for you,
this is what i get?

20:26.934 --> 20:30.234
Nothing personal.
just business.

20:30.300 --> 20:32.334
<i>amateurs tend to ask
for exactly what they want.</i>

20:32.400 --> 20:33.767
Who told you about the kid?

20:33.834 --> 20:36.667
<i>it's like playing poker
with your cards showing.</i>

20:36.734 --> 20:38.834
I think your buddy here
wants to kiss me, finley.

20:38.901 --> 20:40.968
Hey, i'm not that type.

20:41.033 --> 20:42.167
Ugh!

20:42.234 --> 20:43.634
Answer the question.

20:43.701 --> 20:45.100
Sam:
who told you?

20:45.167 --> 20:47.067
A friend of a friend.

20:47.133 --> 20:48.868
I didn't get his name.

20:48.934 --> 20:50.968
They didn't give me details.
i didn't ask for them.

20:51.033 --> 20:53.200
All right, tell me
about this job.

20:53.267 --> 20:55.434
[ sighs ]

20:55.501 --> 20:59.100
They needed help
moving a -- a kid.

20:59.167 --> 21:01.667
They wanted a place
that they could stash him

21:01.734 --> 21:03.400
For a few days
off the street.

21:03.467 --> 21:05.400
I found it.
can i go now?

21:05.467 --> 21:10.734
You can go when i find out
what the hell is going on.

21:10.801 --> 21:12.534
The guy who hired you --

21:12.601 --> 21:14.801
He say when they
were planning this?

21:14.868 --> 21:17.133
Oh, come on, you think
they're gonna tell me when?

21:17.200 --> 21:18.567
Yeah, right after
they told me

21:18.634 --> 21:21.601
Their vacation plans and their
social security numbers.

21:21.667 --> 21:23.334
I don't know.

21:23.400 --> 21:25.367
You got a smart mouth.

21:25.434 --> 21:27.868
Maybe you should start
using it to save your ass.

21:27.934 --> 21:31.868
They told me...
to find a place...

21:31.934 --> 21:33.968
Where they could
stash the kid...

21:34.033 --> 21:35.968
For a few days.

21:36.033 --> 21:37.934
Do you want me
to say that slower?

21:38.000 --> 21:39.167
Where'd you meet them?

21:39.234 --> 21:42.133
Right.
do you think i'm stupid?

21:42.200 --> 21:44.000
I tell you that,

21:44.067 --> 21:46.267
And you're gonna go tell them
and i'm gonna get killed.

21:46.334 --> 21:49.234
You worry about that later.
you got more immediate problems.

21:49.300 --> 21:50.634
Ugh!

21:50.701 --> 21:52.801
[ coughing ]
all right, all right.

21:52.868 --> 21:54.400
All right.

21:54.467 --> 21:57.434
It was a restaurant --
a diner, i think.

21:57.501 --> 21:59.767
<i>when people are desperate
for information,</i>

21:59.834 --> 22:01.534
<i>they start
filling in the blanks,</i>

22:01.601 --> 22:03.968
<i>often without realizing it.</i>

22:04.033 --> 22:06.300
<i>it's something
fortune-tellers rely on.</i>

22:06.367 --> 22:08.267
<i>it works pretty much
the same way for spies.</i>

22:08.334 --> 22:10.367
Think harder.

22:10.434 --> 22:11.734
<i>although fortune-tellers</i>

22:11.801 --> 22:14.834
<i>usually don't get
smacked around as much.</i>

22:14.901 --> 22:16.467
[ groans ]

22:17.767 --> 22:20.000
It was a diner.

22:20.067 --> 22:22.000
It had burgers and fries.

22:22.067 --> 22:24.667
The seaside diner?

22:24.734 --> 22:26.968
Was that it?
off the causeway?

22:27.033 --> 22:28.567
Yes. thank you.

22:28.634 --> 22:31.367
I met the guy
at the seaside diner.

22:32.667 --> 22:34.167
What'd this guy
look like?

22:34.234 --> 22:35.567
Well, i don't know.

22:35.634 --> 22:37.067
H-he was a guy.

22:37.133 --> 22:38.567
Was a white guy, maybe.

22:38.634 --> 22:40.767
"white"?

22:40.834 --> 22:43.334
I'm just gonna go out in miami
and look for a white guy?

22:43.400 --> 22:45.200
You're gonna have to
do better than that.

22:46.467 --> 22:47.801
No! all right, all right,
all right!

22:47.868 --> 22:50.133
It was -- it was --
the waitress knew him.

22:50.200 --> 22:51.968
She called him "flowers."

22:52.033 --> 22:54.534
They knew him there.

22:54.601 --> 22:58.000
And that's it. that's --
that's -- that's all i know.

23:06.567 --> 23:08.033
Man:
yeah, this is jimmy.

23:08.100 --> 23:10.534
Get over to the
seaside diner now.

23:10.601 --> 23:13.934
Ask around for a guy
named flowers.

23:14.000 --> 23:15.133
[ chuckles ]

23:15.200 --> 23:16.567
Surprising how much
a guy remembers

23:16.634 --> 23:18.267
When you help him
out a little.

23:18.334 --> 23:20.534
Listen, this is taking
longer than i thought.

23:20.601 --> 23:26.300
I got to make a call.
you two play nice.

23:26.367 --> 23:28.667
Fi, get over
to the seaside diner.

23:28.734 --> 23:31.234
It's off macarthur causeway.
santora is sending a guy there.

23:31.300 --> 23:33.334
You might be able
to tail him back to brandon.

23:33.400 --> 23:35.467
Just stay out of sight,
all right?

23:35.534 --> 23:36.701
Fiona:
stay out of sight?

23:36.767 --> 23:38.100
You're seriously
telling me that?

23:38.167 --> 23:39.534
Well, it's nothing personal.

23:39.601 --> 23:41.534
Things are just getting
a little tense around here.

23:41.601 --> 23:45.701
So, you and your friends thought
that you could rip me off?

23:45.767 --> 23:48.167
That right? what was
the plan with the kid?

23:48.234 --> 23:50.601
I told you everything i know.
i was supposed to get --

23:50.667 --> 23:51.934
What was the plan?!

23:52.000 --> 23:56.334
I was paid a lousy
150 bucks for this job.

23:56.400 --> 23:57.968
You think i don't
want to tell you?

23:58.033 --> 24:00.167
Put the knife away!!

24:00.234 --> 24:01.868
You've got a sharp knife!!

24:01.934 --> 24:03.567
Michael: get that knife
out of my face!

24:03.634 --> 24:05.734
Fi, just go now.

24:05.801 --> 24:06.767
Aah!

24:06.834 --> 24:08.534
Fine.

24:08.601 --> 24:10.968
You want to --
you want to know the plan?

24:11.033 --> 24:12.133
Yeah, i do.

24:12.200 --> 24:13.701
All right, well,

24:13.767 --> 24:17.067
You're never gonna
know the plan with a knife,

24:17.133 --> 24:21.634
Because cutting me up
ain't gonna turn me
into a mind reader!

24:21.701 --> 24:24.133
Whoa, there, friend.

24:24.200 --> 24:26.767
My prisoner...

24:26.834 --> 24:28.767
My rules, remember?

24:28.834 --> 24:30.434
Now, you want me
to lean on him,

24:30.501 --> 24:32.767
All you have to do is ask.

24:36.901 --> 24:38.067
We clear?

24:38.133 --> 24:40.601
Now, put it away.

24:45.434 --> 24:48.200
[ breathing heavily ]

24:53.818 --> 24:56.150
We may have a lead
on brandon's location.

24:56.217 --> 24:58.050
You're going
to get him now?

24:58.117 --> 24:59.718
If things go
according to plan.

24:59.784 --> 25:01.751
I'll come with you.
i can help.

25:01.818 --> 25:03.718
Well, that's sweet
and very brave,

25:03.784 --> 25:05.883
But you are gonna
get yourself shot.

25:05.950 --> 25:08.617
Well, if that's what it
takes to get our son
back, i don't care.

25:08.684 --> 25:11.050
Brandon is gonna
need you alive.

25:11.117 --> 25:13.050
Getting shot
sounds noble

25:13.117 --> 25:15.150
Until it actually
happens to you.

25:15.217 --> 25:17.883
Don't volunteer for it unless
it's absolutely necessary.

25:17.950 --> 25:20.250
Brandon's gonna be fine.

25:20.317 --> 25:22.617
I know it.

25:22.684 --> 25:25.751
You want to do something
for your son?

25:25.818 --> 25:27.017
Don't forget this moment.

25:28.451 --> 25:30.384
Yeah.

25:30.451 --> 25:32.850
And don't ever
work together.

25:32.917 --> 25:35.517
Not all couples
can handle it.

25:35.584 --> 25:37.983
[ door closes ]

25:38.050 --> 25:39.584
Okay, so,
this flowers --

25:39.651 --> 25:41.551
He show you
where the kid is?

25:41.617 --> 25:43.983
No, t-t-they drove me
through the neighborhood --

25:44.050 --> 25:45.651
T-the route
they were gonna take.

25:45.718 --> 25:46.883
I don't remember --

25:46.950 --> 25:48.417
I've had enough of
you-don't-remember.

25:51.050 --> 25:52.484
No more warnings.

25:52.551 --> 25:54.117
I've answered
all your questions.

25:54.184 --> 25:57.950
I want you to tell me
who is trying to rip me off!

25:58.017 --> 26:00.784
And i want a house
on star island,

26:00.850 --> 26:02.983
Filled with
strippers and bikinis,

26:03.050 --> 26:05.584
But wishing just
doesn't make it so, man!

26:05.651 --> 26:07.284
It's time to focus.

26:07.351 --> 26:10.484
Now, listen, i assume there
isn't a sign on the place

26:10.551 --> 26:11.883
That says "the kid is here,"

26:11.950 --> 26:15.484
So how would he know
if he saw it?

26:15.551 --> 26:17.050
Come on, you got guys
with the kid?

26:17.117 --> 26:18.517
<i>maybe shep saw them.</i>

26:18.584 --> 26:20.917
Yeah, i got two guys.
michael:
yeah, could be.

26:20.983 --> 26:23.617
I saw a couple of guys,
but i didn't talk to them.
i don't know their names.

26:23.684 --> 26:25.751
Did you see the kid?
no.

26:25.818 --> 26:27.950
Okay, santora, so calm down.
he didn't see the kid.

26:28.017 --> 26:29.351
Maybe it's not
the same place.

26:29.417 --> 26:31.451
He didn't see him
because the kid

26:31.517 --> 26:33.983
Is in a shed
behind the house!

26:34.050 --> 26:36.117
Now shut up
and let me think!

26:41.917 --> 26:44.684
<i>searching for a concealed enemy
who could be anywhere</i>

26:44.751 --> 26:46.050
<i>is a waste of time.</i>

26:46.117 --> 26:47.517
Yeah, it's jimmy.

26:50.551 --> 26:52.784
Nobody's heard of "flowers"
at the diner.

26:52.850 --> 26:56.417
<i>usually, your best bet
is to stay put</i>

26:56.484 --> 26:58.950
<i>and give your enemy
a reason to come to you.</i>

27:01.317 --> 27:02.417
What's going on?

27:02.484 --> 27:04.751
Is there something
i should know about?

27:04.818 --> 27:06.517
Don't worry about it.

27:06.584 --> 27:09.017
Just get back to the house
and watch the kid.
[ camera shutter clicks ]

27:15.350 --> 27:18.884
<i>to tail someone, you need
both skill and instinct.</i>

27:18.951 --> 27:21.483
<i>you need skill
because the driving is tough.</i>

27:21.550 --> 27:23.084
<i>you can't get too close,</i>

27:23.151 --> 27:24.917
<i>and you can't drift
too far away.</i>

27:24.984 --> 27:27.617
<i>you can't go too fast
or too slow.</i>

27:27.684 --> 27:29.851
<i>you need instinct
because every turn,</i>

27:29.917 --> 27:32.650
<i>every lane change, every bridge
raises the risk of being seen.</i>

27:34.483 --> 27:36.750
<i>anyone can be trained
to follow a car.</i>

27:36.817 --> 27:38.184
<i>but it takes good instincts</i>

27:38.251 --> 27:40.184
<i>to know when it's time
to stop following.</i>

27:46.017 --> 27:49.784
So, i had one of my guys
ask around.

27:49.851 --> 27:51.318
No one at that restaurant

27:51.383 --> 27:53.117
Ever heard of anyone
named flowers.

27:53.184 --> 27:55.117
Why is that m-my fault?

27:55.184 --> 27:57.951
Maybe he went
to the wrong place.

27:58.017 --> 28:00.350
He went to the diner,
you lying son of a bitch.

28:00.417 --> 28:02.984
Why would i lie to you?

28:03.051 --> 28:04.550
That's it.

28:04.617 --> 28:08.984
I'm shutting this thing down
before it gets any worse.

28:09.051 --> 28:10.884
<i>when you work
with someone long enough,</i>

28:10.951 --> 28:12.851
<i>you learn to trust them.</i>

28:12.917 --> 28:15.017
<i>when things go bad,</i>

28:15.084 --> 28:18.483
<i>that trust is the difference
between life and death.</i>

28:18.550 --> 28:22.051
<i>of course, knowing that doesn't
make it less terrifying</i>

28:22.117 --> 28:24.017
<i>to back a play
you know nothing about.</i>

28:24.084 --> 28:26.184
Listen, uh...

28:26.251 --> 28:28.350
I know this guy, shep.

28:28.417 --> 28:31.550
I mean, he's a pain in the ass,
but his information is good.

28:31.617 --> 28:34.717
Yeah? because he told
me some story about a
guy who doesn't exist?

28:34.784 --> 28:36.717
Maybe the guy does exist.

28:36.784 --> 28:38.450
He could be one
of your own guys.

28:44.584 --> 28:46.717
So, one more time...

28:46.784 --> 28:50.017
This flowers guy...

28:50.084 --> 28:51.350
What did he look like?

28:53.383 --> 28:56.851
He has, uh,
slicked-back hair.

28:56.917 --> 28:58.750
He was a muscle guy.

29:00.218 --> 29:01.617
Uh...

29:01.684 --> 29:03.251
He wears
those muscle shirts,

29:03.318 --> 29:04.984
You know,
to show off his arms.

29:05.051 --> 29:07.483
That's the best i can do.
that's all i got.

29:07.550 --> 29:09.817
That's flowers?
you're sure?

29:09.884 --> 29:13.784
Yeah, that's the guy
who told me about the kid.

29:18.051 --> 29:18.917
Ugh!

29:18.984 --> 29:19.817
Hey, hey!

29:22.550 --> 29:24.151
What is wrong
with you?

29:24.218 --> 29:25.650
Santora:
that's my guy.

29:25.717 --> 29:29.151
Like you said, my own guy
is trying to steal from me.

29:29.218 --> 29:30.483
What guy?

29:30.550 --> 29:32.251
His name's jimmy.

29:32.318 --> 29:34.517
The guy i sent to the diner
to look for flowers --

29:34.584 --> 29:36.750
<i>it turns out the son
of a bitch is flowers.</i>

29:36.817 --> 29:38.350
He's supposed to be
watching the kid.

29:38.417 --> 29:41.917
Instead, he's planning
to rip me off.

29:41.984 --> 29:43.784
You know,
you can call it off.

29:43.851 --> 29:45.350
Let the kid go.

29:45.417 --> 29:46.817
Hell, just give him to me.

29:46.884 --> 29:48.784
I'll tell his parents i found
him wandering around.

29:48.851 --> 29:50.318
It's too late for that.

29:50.383 --> 29:53.350
He saw my face.
it's over.

29:53.417 --> 29:54.917
I got to clean
this whole mess up.

29:56.251 --> 29:58.084
Whoa, whoa, what are you
gonna with that?

29:58.151 --> 30:00.383
Listen, you've been
a stand-up guy.

30:00.450 --> 30:01.717
I appreciate that.

30:01.784 --> 30:03.584
And i don't want
to cause you problems.

30:03.650 --> 30:06.051
But that guy
in there, shep...

30:06.117 --> 30:07.417
He's got to die.

30:10.051 --> 30:11.184
Now.

30:18.451 --> 30:20.017
<i>every profession
has occupational hazards.</i>

30:20.751 --> 30:22.384
<i>butchers cut themselves,</i>

30:22.451 --> 30:24.217
<i>house painters
fall off ladders,</i>

30:24.284 --> 30:27.217
<i>and operatives get asked
to help kill their own people.</i>

30:27.284 --> 30:29.717
[ laughing ] hey.
you watch it, friend.

30:29.784 --> 30:31.918
I got unis checking
on my interview.

30:31.983 --> 30:32.950
Back off.

30:33.017 --> 30:34.217
This is my snitch.

30:34.284 --> 30:36.884
I got to be able
to explain what goes on.

30:36.950 --> 30:38.417
My own guys
are turning on me.

30:38.484 --> 30:39.651
If he's part of it,
he's got to go.

30:39.717 --> 30:40.818
They all do.

30:40.884 --> 30:42.617
Oh, i see, so i'm just
supposed to sit back

30:42.684 --> 30:44.284
And hope none of this
blows back on me?

30:44.350 --> 30:46.517
No way, pal.
that's not how this goes down.

30:46.584 --> 30:48.451
You got any ideas?
i'm listening.

30:50.818 --> 30:52.284
Yeah.

30:52.350 --> 30:54.451
Yeah, i say that, uh...

30:54.517 --> 30:56.150
Dropped him off by the road.

30:56.217 --> 30:58.284
I let him out 'cause
he was sick from the dope.

30:58.350 --> 31:00.384
I'll just tell them that --
that he attacked me,

31:00.451 --> 31:01.950
And he tried to escape.

31:02.017 --> 31:03.250
Wait, you?

31:03.317 --> 31:05.384
Yeah. don't you remember?
he's my prisoner.

31:05.451 --> 31:06.950
How am i gonna
explain a suspect

31:07.017 --> 31:08.950
That's full of these
random bullet holes?

31:09.017 --> 31:12.050
We'll have the damn fbi here.
it's better this way.

31:12.117 --> 31:13.851
Put a few rounds
in his chest with my gun,

31:13.918 --> 31:16.017
But you do it out by the road,
you understand?

31:16.083 --> 31:19.317
Your gun? what the hell
are you talking about?

31:19.384 --> 31:22.651
Look, i got to be able to sell
this story to my department.

31:22.717 --> 31:24.517
If i don't,
they're coming after me.

31:24.584 --> 31:26.818
Trust me,
it's better this way.

31:26.884 --> 31:28.651
Come on, come on.

31:31.918 --> 31:33.384
All right.

31:33.451 --> 31:35.451
I'll go get shep.

31:35.517 --> 31:37.584
You get your guy on the phone.
you tell him to sit tight.

31:37.651 --> 31:41.284
I don't want this situation
any worse than it already is.

31:44.983 --> 31:48.150
[ groans ]

31:48.217 --> 31:50.417
[ both grunt ]

31:50.484 --> 31:52.017
Michael: oh!

31:52.083 --> 31:53.584
You all right, mike?

31:53.651 --> 31:56.950
Yeah. you still pack
a pretty good punch, sam.

31:57.017 --> 31:59.284
Yeah, well,
the good news is

31:59.350 --> 32:02.684
Santora's planning on
going back to the kid.

32:02.751 --> 32:05.384
Fi followed their guy.

32:05.451 --> 32:07.851
They're holed up on an island
off the causeway.

32:07.918 --> 32:09.384
And the bad news?

32:09.451 --> 32:13.551
Santora wants
to kill you first.

32:13.617 --> 32:15.983
I convinced him
to do it with my gun

32:16.050 --> 32:17.317
Up on the side
of the road,

32:17.384 --> 32:19.284
Make it look like you
were trying to get away.

32:19.350 --> 32:20.417
How far is the road?

32:20.484 --> 32:21.918
A couple hundred yards.

32:21.983 --> 32:23.284
I guess it'll have to do.

32:23.350 --> 32:24.484
Mike, if there was
any other way...

32:24.551 --> 32:25.918
There isn't.

32:25.983 --> 32:27.651
All right,
when you get free,

32:27.717 --> 32:29.684
Take his car
and head to the causeway.

32:29.751 --> 32:31.851
I'll get you the address.

32:31.918 --> 32:33.651
Good luck, mikey.

32:33.717 --> 32:35.117
Santora: hey.

32:35.184 --> 32:37.317
Let's take a walk.

32:40.818 --> 32:43.717
Listen, listen,
you don't want to do this.

32:43.784 --> 32:45.384
This -- i could
tell you more.

32:45.451 --> 32:47.818
I could tell you about
flowers and the plan.

32:47.884 --> 32:49.484
Man, you don't
want to do this.

32:49.551 --> 32:50.717
I know plenty already.

32:50.784 --> 32:52.451
I mean,
why shut this down?

32:52.517 --> 32:54.651
There's money
to be made here, man.

32:54.717 --> 32:56.451
I-i could help you.
we could split it 50/50.

32:56.517 --> 32:57.983
[ laughing ] oh, yeah?

32:58.050 --> 33:01.317
[ sobbing ] i don't
want to die, man!

33:01.384 --> 33:02.684
Please...

33:02.751 --> 33:04.117
Please, i'm begging you!

33:12.317 --> 33:14.417
[ grunting ]

33:18.083 --> 33:19.918
[ grunting stops ]

33:23.517 --> 33:24.784
[ coughs ]

33:35.117 --> 33:36.751
[ tires squeal ]

33:43.217 --> 33:46.150
He got away.

33:46.217 --> 33:48.284
What the hell
are you talking about?

33:48.350 --> 33:49.517
Where's my gun?

33:49.584 --> 33:50.784
He took it!

33:50.851 --> 33:54.384
He's got my gun?
we got to find him! now!

33:56.950 --> 33:58.651
Could he be going
to meet up with jimmy?

33:58.717 --> 34:00.250
I don't know. maybe.

34:00.317 --> 34:02.050
And you told jimmy
to stay put with the kid?

34:02.117 --> 34:03.517
Yeah.
where's the house?

34:04.884 --> 34:07.451
We don't have time for this!
where's the house?!

34:07.517 --> 34:09.083
Hibiscus island.

34:09.150 --> 34:10.617
What address?

34:10.684 --> 34:13.650
I got to know!
they got my gun!

34:13.717 --> 34:15.918
Look, if i go down
for this, so do you!

34:15.983 --> 34:19.050
1313 prospect street.
what are you doing?

34:19.117 --> 34:22.284
They have a security office
on the island.

34:22.350 --> 34:23.583
I'll ask
if they've seen him.

34:23.650 --> 34:25.050
[ ringing ]

34:25.117 --> 34:26.684
[ cellphone ringing ]

34:26.751 --> 34:28.284
Yeah, sam?

34:28.350 --> 34:30.650
Yeah, this is officer finley,
uh, miami p.d.

34:30.717 --> 34:32.650
I'd like to know
if you've seen anyone

34:32.717 --> 34:34.516
Go to 1313 prospect street.

34:34.583 --> 34:37.983
Uh, there's someone
going there right now.

34:38.050 --> 34:39.851
[ dialing ]

34:39.918 --> 34:42.516
Fi, i got the address.

34:42.583 --> 34:44.583
[ tires screech ]

34:49.150 --> 34:51.350
[ gun cocks ]

34:51.417 --> 34:54.884
<i>people underestimate
the tactical importance of tv</i>

34:54.949 --> 34:56.583
<i>in urban warfare.</i>

34:56.650 --> 34:59.884
<i>guard duty's boring, and a
ballgame passes the time better</i>

34:59.950 --> 35:02.617
<i>than, say,
looking for intruders.</i>

35:02.684 --> 35:05.150
<i>more battles have been
decided by pennant races</i>

35:05.217 --> 35:07.083
<i>than people imagine.</i>

35:07.150 --> 35:09.117
[ muffled shouting ]

35:11.350 --> 35:12.751
Fiona: brandon?

35:12.818 --> 35:14.818
We're gonna take you back
to your mom and dad, okay?

35:43.950 --> 35:46.083
Santora:
the junkie's here.

35:46.150 --> 35:48.584
We do him and jimmy first,
then the kid.

35:48.651 --> 35:50.050
Okay, you cut
through the backyard,

35:50.117 --> 35:51.184
I'll cover you
from the front?

35:51.250 --> 35:53.717
Okay.

35:55.350 --> 35:57.784
Have fun in there,
you son of a bitch.

36:00.384 --> 36:02.350
Look who's here.

36:02.417 --> 36:04.284
<i>[ indistinct tv chatter ]</i>

36:04.350 --> 36:05.818
You thought you could
steal from me?

36:05.884 --> 36:07.751
What the hell
are you saying?
where's the kid?

36:07.818 --> 36:08.884
I said
where's the kid?!

36:08.950 --> 36:10.751
I don't know!
he was just there!

36:10.818 --> 36:12.150
I know what
you did, jimmy.

36:12.217 --> 36:13.950
I know you're flowers.
i know everything.

36:14.017 --> 36:16.784
I don't know what you're
talking about. get that
thing out of my face!

36:16.851 --> 36:20.451
Put it down now! you picked
the wrong guy to double-cross!

36:20.517 --> 36:22.484
I did everything
you ever said!
you sold me out
to a junkie!

36:22.551 --> 36:24.918
<i>it's always best to have
business arguments unarmed.</i>

36:24.983 --> 36:28.884
<i>when tempers are high
and everyone's got a gun,</i>

36:28.950 --> 36:31.184
<i>you never know what's
going to set someone off.</i>

36:31.250 --> 36:32.717
[ gunshot ]

36:32.784 --> 36:34.784
[ gunshots ]

36:34.851 --> 36:37.784
Jimmy, jimmy, don't --
[ gunshots ]

36:42.551 --> 36:43.884
I don't know
what to say.

36:43.950 --> 36:45.284
You don't have to
say anything.

36:45.350 --> 36:46.918
Think about leaving miami.

36:46.983 --> 36:49.150
You don't want to be
around if santora's
friends come looking.

36:49.217 --> 36:50.617
Oh, we weren't
planning to be.

36:50.684 --> 36:53.017
We've, uh, talked about
making a fresh start

36:53.083 --> 36:55.451
Somewhere else,
together.

36:55.517 --> 36:57.484
Patricia: thank you...

36:57.551 --> 36:59.217
For everything.

36:59.284 --> 37:01.584
You ready?

37:01.651 --> 37:02.884
[ chuckles ]

37:06.150 --> 37:09.717
A fresh start...together.

37:09.784 --> 37:11.784
Kind of inspiring,
don't you think?

37:11.851 --> 37:13.083
I'd settle for
staying out of jail.

37:14.684 --> 37:16.684
Come on, fi,
we got a date...

37:16.751 --> 37:18.651
With the storage unit.

37:21.017 --> 37:24.417
[ indistinct radio chatter ]

37:38.717 --> 37:40.651
<i>when a front door
is being watched,</i>

37:40.717 --> 37:43.884
<i>your best option oftentimes
is just to make a back door.</i>

37:46.800 --> 37:49.134
<i>if you don't mind getting damp,</i>

37:49.200 --> 37:51.933
<i>a water saw is a great tool
for the job.</i>

37:52.000 --> 37:54.000
<i>it will cut through the wall</i>

37:54.067 --> 37:55.900
<i>much more quietly
than a metal saw</i>

37:55.967 --> 37:57.734
<i>and won't ignite
anything flammable</i>

37:57.800 --> 37:59.800
<i>that happens
to be lying around.</i>

38:51.833 --> 38:54.134
Hey, detective, uh,
would you like to come in?

38:54.200 --> 38:56.334
I have
some more receipts.

38:56.401 --> 38:57.867
Cute.

38:57.933 --> 39:00.067
You know, i finally did get
a look at that storage unit

39:00.134 --> 39:01.567
That didn't belong to you.

39:01.634 --> 39:04.401
Find anything interesting?

39:04.467 --> 39:06.833
Yeah, i found a hole
in the back of the wall

39:06.900 --> 39:08.567
And a puddle
of water inside.

39:08.634 --> 39:10.434
Yeah, the heavy rains
the other night

39:10.501 --> 39:12.434
Must have done
some funny things.

39:12.501 --> 39:15.000
This isn't over.

39:20.967 --> 39:22.234
[ exhales sharply ]

39:39.833 --> 39:41.134
Did you make this?

39:41.200 --> 39:42.267
You like it?

39:42.334 --> 39:45.000
I wanted this to be special,
so i cooked.

39:45.067 --> 39:46.967
It's good.

39:47.034 --> 39:49.034
[ laughs ]

39:55.234 --> 39:56.534
Happy birthday, mike.

39:56.601 --> 39:58.833
Beer. a five-pack.
thanks.

39:58.900 --> 40:00.833
Yeah, it's imported.

40:00.900 --> 40:03.334
It's supposed to be brewed
by some monks in belgium.

40:03.401 --> 40:04.668
It's, uh...

40:04.734 --> 40:07.334
It's really good,
or, you know, so i heard.

40:07.401 --> 40:08.534
Would you like some?

40:08.601 --> 40:10.567
Yeah, thanks.

40:10.634 --> 40:11.867
Sam:
it's kind of pricy,

40:11.933 --> 40:13.800
But i figured only
the best for you, mike.

40:13.867 --> 40:15.768
Would you like
a bottle opener, sam?

40:15.833 --> 40:18.034
Oh, no, no, i got one.
thanks. yeah.

40:18.100 --> 40:19.701
I never leave home
without it.

40:19.768 --> 40:21.434
Sam, you need
a bottle opener.

40:21.501 --> 40:22.867
Why don't i show you
where it is?

40:24.367 --> 40:25.501
[ sighs ]

40:25.567 --> 40:27.900
Okay. sure.

40:37.900 --> 40:39.601
[ clears throat ]

40:55.401 --> 40:56.800
It's a bayonet.

40:56.867 --> 40:59.467
Used during the first
world war for close fighting.

40:59.534 --> 41:01.367
Fi...

41:01.434 --> 41:02.634
Thanks?

41:02.701 --> 41:04.067
Well, someone once told me

41:04.134 --> 41:06.833
That caring for you
is like trench warfare.

41:11.834 --> 41:13.834
So I thought you should arm yourself.

